This paper proposes an approach for automated program classification using bilateral tree-based convolutional neural networks (BiTBCNNs). The paper focuses on the application of machine learning techniques to programming languages, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with software engineering (SE) and programming languages (PL), which are also relevant sub-categories. The paper also uses convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which are commonly used in computer vision (CV) and image processing (IP), making cs.CL (Computation and Language) another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper uses deep learning techniques, which are relevant to artificial intelligence (AI), making cs.AI another possible sub-category.
